Villain is loose-passive (VPIP 54%, PFR 6%) — they limp/call a lot and fold to c-bets 55% of the time. With **Ac6c** in the BB against a passive SB caller, I have a solid suited ace. Raising here builds the pot with equity advantage and sets up profitable c-bet opportunities postflop given villain's fold-to-cbet tendency.

I'll raise to 8 (4x pot-sized raise).

